Field Detail

machineOpTable

public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,char[]> machineOpTable
The machineOpTable is a hash map with the key being a string of the instruction and the value as a character array. The format of the array is as follows: Position 0: hex value of instruction Position 1: 0,1,2,3 depending on the number of operands the instruction has

psuedoOpTable

public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer> psuedoOpTable
The pseudoOpTable is a hash map with the key being the instruction as a string and the value of the number of operands as an integer.

symbolTable

public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String[]> symbolTable
The symbolTable is a hash map that has the label as the string key and the value as a string array. The format of the array is as follows: Position 0: A hex string representing the location/value of that label Position 1: Ò0Ó for absolute or Ò1Ó for relative

literalTable

public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String[]> literalTable
The literalTable is a hash map with the key being ÒxHEXÓ/Ó#DECÓ as a string. The value in the map is a string array with pos 0 being the hex value of the literal (string length 4).

passOnePgoffsetCheck

public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer[]> passOnePgoffsetCheck
This sets a value of the last 9 bits of the value concatenated with the first seven bits of the location couner.
